00:24:40.560 --> 00:24:47.680
So, one here is, could you remind us what the package is that has the tidy models default

00:24:47.680 --> 00:24:49.359
tuning parameter recommendations?

00:24:49.920 --> 00:24:52.959
I can't remember if it's an add-in or if it's an actual package.

00:24:53.760 --> 00:25:00.959
So, the package that contains the information that tells the rest of tidy models how to

00:25:00.959 --> 00:25:09.920
tune parameters, that package is called dials, and you can learn about it at dials.tidymodels.org.

00:25:11.359 --> 00:25:15.199
So, that package contains information about tuning parameters.

00:25:16.000 --> 00:25:22.880
And anywhere else in the tidy models, if you say, I want to tune for a particular parameter,

00:25:23.359 --> 00:25:29.040
the number of trees, tidy models will ask dials, okay, what do we know about the number

00:25:29.040 --> 00:25:30.959
of trees as a tuning parameter?

00:25:32.160 --> 00:25:37.439
And what option should we try out to get that tuning parameter right?

00:25:38.160 --> 00:25:42.400
And then dials will tell tidy models what values to try out.

00:25:43.680 --> 00:25:50.160
And you can add all sorts of custom configurations to how dials will provide those

00:25:50.160 --> 00:25:50.880
recommendations.

00:25:52.959 --> 00:25:54.239
